From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 10:56:04 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add default-disabled GRX Route B rd_native fused_post_chain
 in-frame fusion-first replacement
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Stacked on 0001..0029 + 0040 + 0041 + 0042 + 0043 + 0044 (the branch-HEAD
gpu_culling tail plus the tonemap, ssao_blur, taa_resolve, particles_copy and
cluster_store rd_native slices). This is the sixth Route B replacement slice and
the FUSION-FIRST leg of the two-level fallback contract: fused rd_native ->
single-pass tonemap rd_native (patch 0040, already in this stack) -> native Godot
tonemap chain. It is SELF-CONTAINED on the culling tail — the fused shim scaffold
(0036-0038) lives on the mutually-exclusive fused tail (see PATCH_ALLOCATION.md
double-tail note) and is NOT in this stack, so 0045 adds its own bridge-
independent backend selector and cascades into 0040's tonemap rd_native rather
than a fused shim gate.

- drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h: new default-false virtual
  try_record_fused_post_chain_rd_native(RID src_color, RID lum_source,
  RID prev_luminance, RID dst_color, RID dst_luminance, Size2i source_size,
  Size2i dest_size, float exposure, float white, float luminance_multiplier). It
  takes the five Godot texture RID handles in the container's binding order
  (src_color/lum_source/prev_luminance = SRV t0..t2, dst_color/dst_luminance =
  UAV u0/u1) instead of native ID3D12Resource* handles. Base returns false.
- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: two new default-safe settings
  (rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/backend, int default 0, and
  .../rd_container_path, string default ""). Defaults keep it disabled.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.{h,cpp}: try_record_fused_post_chain_rd_native
  override plus its own 64-byte b0 / 5-resource constants
  (RD_NATIVE_FUSED_POST_CHAIN_ROOT_CONSTANT_BYTES / _RESOURCE_COUNT), distinct
  from the fused-tail FUSED_POST_CHAIN_RESOURCE_MAPPING_* so the two tails never
  collide. Lazily builds the pipeline, runs a usage-bits preflight (three SRV
  SAMPLING_BIT, two UAV STORAGE_BIT), binds the five textures via UniformSetCacheRD
  (t0..t2 TEXTURE, u0/u1 IMAGE), packs the 64-byte b0 ([i64 source dims, i64
  lum_source dims, then max/min_luminance, exposure_adjust, exposure, white,
  luminance_multiplier, first_frame, auto_exposure_scale]), and dispatches
  ceil(dest/8) groups on its own compute list. It FAILS CLOSED (honest measured
  boundary) when lum_source == prev_luminance or dst_color == dst_luminance: the
  distinct double-buffered luminance-final targets are NOT exposed by the public
  Luminance API at the tonemap call site, and binding an aliased/degenerate
  luminance UAV would corrupt the feedback loop or risk a mid-frame
  uniform_set_create assert, so it cascades to the patch 0040 tonemap rd_native
  single-pass fallback. The one-shot RXGD_RD_NATIVE_FUSED_POST_CHAIN active marker
  is emitted only when a genuine distinct-target replacement is recorded.
- servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
  _render_buffers_post_process_and_tonemap: in the can_use_storage tonemap block,
  backend == 2 runs the fusion-first rd_native gate BEFORE the patch 0040 tonemap
  rd_native gate; a successful record skips the tonemap rd_native gate, the shim
  gate and the native tonemapper. backend != 2 leaves the pre-existing 0040 +
  shim + native chain byte-for-byte unchanged.

Fail-closed everywhere: with the default backend == 0 (and empty container path),
the fused gate never engages and the tonemap rd_native / native chain renders. On
the culling tail the fused luminance-final double-buffer binding is unavailable
(deferred Luminance-API extension, PASS_CONTRACT 3.4/5), so this gate fails closed
at the aliasing guard and cascades to tonemap rd_native today; it lifts
automatically once distinct luminance targets are supplied. RXGD_ABI_VERSION is
unchanged (no C ABI struct change, no RxGdCaps.flags bit; rd_native is bridge-
independent). No performance claim is made.
